---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Show HN draft per BRAND.md §Show HN Voice:
//   - Title pattern: `Show HN: feedbackmonk – <one-line value prop>`
//   - Open with the artifact, not the founder story.
//   - One concrete technical detail (the widget bundle size + the
//     CI-enforced tracker scan).
//   - Direct, evidenced, no marketing-speak. ~150-250 words.
//
// frontmatter draft:true — page is unlisted (no nav link).
// User reviews and revises before posting per DEC-FBR-10 Stage 2 trigger.
const draftTitle = 'Show HN: feedbackmonk – privacy-first product feedback (AGPL)';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Show HN draft"
  description="Working draft of the Show HN announcement post for feedbackmonk. Not yet published."
>
  <article class="hn-draft">
    <header>
      <p class="draft-tag">DRAFT &mdash; not yet posted</p>
      <h1>Show HN draft</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        This is the working draft of the Show HN announcement. It will get
        a final pass from the maintainer before the launch.
      </p>
    </header>

    <hr />

    <section aria-labelledby="post-title">
      <h2 id="post-title">{draftTitle}</h2>

      <p>
        feedbackmonk is a small, open-source feedback platform: an
        embeddable widget, a triage admin, a public roadmap with voting,
        and status emails. AGPL-3.0; self-host with
        <code>docker compose up</code>, or run on our SaaS.
      </p>

      <p>
        Source: <a href="https://github.com/feedbackmonk/feedbackmonk">github.com/feedbackmonk/feedbackmonk</a><br />
        Self-host docs: <a href="https://feedbackmonk.com/docs/self-host">feedbackmonk.com/docs/self-host</a>
      </p>

      <p>
        I built it because the existing feedback tools either bundle a
        tracker on every embed (Intercom, Hotjar, similar) or sit behind
        SSO-and-seat-licensing walls that are wrong for indie shops. The
        positioning is "Plausible Analytics for product feedback":
        privacy-respecting, source-available, runs in your tenant.
      </p>

      <p>
        Two things worth surfacing for the dev audience:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>
          The widget bundle is <strong>16.8&nbsp;KB</strong> (45% under the
          30&nbsp;KB hard cap). A CI oracle scans every <code>dist/*</code>
          artifact against an 18-hostname tracker allowlist on every
          build &mdash; "zero third-party trackers" is enforced at build
          time, not aspirational copy. See the
          <a href="https://github.com/feedbackmonk/feedbackmonk/tree/main/.claude/oracles/widget-bundle-size">widget-bundle-size</a>
          oracle.
        </li>
        <li>
          End-user identity is whatever your app's JWT says &mdash; no
          callbacks to your auth provider, no long-lived bearer tokens,
          no cookies on the user's root domain. If you don't sign a
          JWT, the widget submits anonymously via a first-party cookie
          scoped to the API domain.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        v1 is intentionally small: feedback submission, status workflow,
        public roadmap with voting, status emails. No webhooks yet, no
        Polar billing checkout yet (mailto stub until we wire it), no
        dark mode in admin (v1.1). The roadmap is on the site &mdash;
        you can vote on it.
      </p>

      <p>
        Stack: Rust (axum) on top of postgres, vanilla TypeScript widget,
        React admin, Astro marketing. Migrations are sqlx; multi-tenancy
        is enforced via a repository layer that's the sole query path.
        About 18k LoC total.
      </p>

      <p>
        Happy to answer questions about the design trade-offs &mdash;
        why text-only wordmark in v1, why AGPL rather than MIT, why
        we ship a Self-host tier on day one rather than gating it behind
        a contract. The decision log is in the repo
        (<a href="https://github.com/feedbackmonk/feedbackmonk/blob/main/docs/specs/DECISIONS.md">docs/specs/DECISIONS.md</a>).
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section aria-labelledby="post-notes">
      <h2 id="post-notes">Authoring notes (not part of the post)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Title is set in <code>--brand-mono</code> for visual separation from the page chrome.</li>
        <li>Word count: ~280 (slightly over the BRAND.md 150&ndash;250 guidance; maintainer to trim during revision pass).</li>
        <li>BRAND.md ban-list check: no "leverage / synergize / robust / world-class / cutting-edge / paradigm / holistic / ecosystem / journey / empower" used. No exclamation points in body.</li>
        <li>Includes the one concrete technical detail per BRAND.md (widget bundle size + tracker oracle).</li>
        <li>Acknowledges limits per voice guideline 5 (Honest about limits): no webhooks, no Polar checkout, no dark mode.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hn-draft {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .draft-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--brand-sage-deep);
    background: var(--brand-rule);
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: var(--brand-radius);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  hr {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  .hn-draft h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
